# Redesign EditJournal to match Editor.jsx overlay UI

## Context
EditJournal currently renders as a small absolute-positioned overlay **inside** each `.postcards-grid-item` card. The user wants it to render as a full-screen overlay modal at the `.profile-parent-container` level, matching the Editor.jsx layout and UI.

## Files to Modify

1. **`client/src/components/HomePage/postCards/ProfilePostCards/editJournal.jsx`** ŌĆö Restructure JSX + classes to match Editor.jsx
2. **`client/src/components/HomePage/postCards/ProfilePostCards/profilepostcards.css`** ŌĆö Replace old edit-journal styles with Editor-matching overlay styles
3. **`client/src/components/HomePage/postCards/ProfilePostCards/ProfilePostCards.jsx`** ŌĆö Move EditJournal render out of map loop, use portal to `.profile-parent-container`

## Changes

### 1. ProfilePostCards.jsx ŌĆö Portal rendering

- Import `createPortal` from `react-dom`
- Remove the two `<EditJournal>` renders from inside the grid-view map (line 309-311) and list-view map (line 446-448)
- Add a single EditJournal render **outside** both view loops, using `createPortal` to target `.profile-parent-container`:

```jsx
{showEditor !== null && createPortal(
    <AnimatePresence>
        <EditJournal journalData={journalData ?? {}} onClose={handleClickCloseEditor} />
    </AnimatePresence>,
    document.querySelector('.profile-parent-container')
)}
```

### 2. editJournal.jsx ŌĆö Match Editor.jsx structure

Restructure the component to follow the Editor's visual hierarchy. It already imports `editor.css` (line 3), so all Editor classes are available.

**New JSX structure:**
```
<div className="editor-parent-container">          ŌåÉ full overlay backdrop with blur
  <motion.div className="editor-container">         ŌåÉ centered modal card (720px, 80% height)
    <div className="editor-close-bttn-container">   ŌåÉ right-aligned close button
      <button className="editor-close-bttn">X</button>
    </div>

    <input className="content-title-input" />        ŌåÉ large serif title, bottom-border focus

    <LexicalComposer>
      <div className="toolbar-wrapper">              ŌåÉ sticky toolbar
        <ToolBar />
      </div>
      <div className="editor-loader-wrapper">        ŌåÉ bar loader during save
        <BarLoader />
      </div>
      <div className="editor-shell">                 ŌåÉ scrollable editor content
        <RichTextPlugin />
        <ImagePlugin />
        <HistoryPlugin />
        <OnChangePlugin />
      </div>
      <div className="editor-footer">               ŌåÉ footer with save button
        <span></span>
        <button className="editor-save-bttn">Save edit</button>
      </div>
    </LexicalComposer>
  </motion.div>
</div>
```

Key changes:
- Wrap everything in `.editor-parent-container` (backdrop + blur overlay)
- Use `.editor-container` for the centered modal card
- Replace custom close button with `.editor-close-bttn-container` + `.editor-close-bttn`
- Replace `.edit-joutnal-title-input` with `.content-title-input` (serif, bottom-border)
- Add `.editor-footer` with save button styled as `.editor-save-bttn`
- Remove the "Important Notes" section (unnecessary UI noise)
- Keep the same save logic and LexicalComposer instance

### 3. profilepostcards.css ŌĆö Clean up old styles

Remove the old edit-journal-specific CSS (lines ~683-812):
- `.edit-journal-container` and its rules
- `.edit-journal-header-container`, `.edit-journal-header`
- `.first-child-header-container`, `.second-child-header-container`
- `.save-edit-button`
- `.edit-journal-close-bttn`
- `.edit-joutnal-title-input`
